  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The first mission was coming to the edge early in the morning.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was raining.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We had some tents on us, and then staying on the edge, observing the traffic over the r-- over the lines, waiting for dusk because there was at least 500 yards, maybe more, between the edge of the forest and the-- and the embankment.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Watching the traffic, not going out in daylight because the Germans usually had a machine gun nest on a flat car ahead of the engine and one behind.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Waiting for the night, we set up two positions.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "A typical attack is that you set up flanking positions, and then the center crew goes forward, lays the mine, arms it, but does not attach it to the rail because it's the train.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It's not, you know, pushing a plunger and blowing it up the way-- the way you see John Wayne movies.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "The partisan trick is to have the train do the explosion itself by place-- place-- placing the blasting cap on the outside flange of the rail so that when it gets hit, it gets ignited.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And then you put in about a certain amount of cord in insufficient time, assuming the speed is about 20 kilometers an hour, that it would blow up halfway after the front wheel.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That's right, and this is why a professional is so useful.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "One of the tragedies of much of the partisan warfare that has been waged, both in Western Europe and in Eastern Europe, was that the professional know-how just wasn't there.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the, the conventional armies did not know how to do it.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I mean, in those days, there was no such thing as special forces.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
